question.text: When 12H<sup>+</sup> pass through <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0–</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> particle, how many <math><mtext>ATPs</mtext></math> are produced?

solution.text: The energy released during the electron system is utilized in synthesizing ATP with the help of ATP synthase enzyme (complex V). This complex consists of two major components: <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> and F0. For each ATP produced, 2H<sup>+</sup> pass through <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math> from the intermembrane space to the matrix down the electrochemical proton gradient.
